text:【和死神赛跑切磋救命绝招，中日韩医生火速联合会诊】死亡率是判断一个疾病危害的重要指标。新冠肺炎疫情中，危重症病人的绝对数量和治疗困难有目共睹。在@田薇_TianWei 主持的 #全球疫情会诊室# 里，东北亚三国前线医生直面新冠肺炎死亡率难题。日本进入老龄社会，一旦疫情全面暴发，危重症患者的比例势必飞涨；韩国疫情暴发迅速，危重病人洪水般涌向医院。政府被迫打造中央控制体系，全国统一安排就医，解燃眉之急；中国武汉医生周宁对死亡的认识最为深刻。数周以来他一直奋战在ICU，用呼吸机、人工肺抢等救助危重症病人。三位医生沟通高效，跨时空讨论实事求是。如今，他们已各自继续奔赴“战场”. The mortality rate is an important indicator to judge the harm of a disease. Frontline doctors from three northeast Asian countries confront the challenges in dealing with COVID-19. Japan as an aging society, saw the proportion of severe patients soar after the epidemic. The outbreak in South Korea has been rapid, with severe patients flooding hospitals. The government has been forced to create a central control system and arrange medical treatment throughout the country to meet urgent needs. Zhou Ning, a doctor in Wuhan, knows death best. He has been in the ICU for weeks, using ventilators, ECMO and other devices to help critical patients. The three doctors communicate effectively across time and space. #全球战疫总动员# http://t.cn/A6z4Frzz
